Pre-Game Insights: Australia meets Pakistan in Dubai for a chance at World Cup glory.
Australia takes on Pakistan in Dubai at 1am AEDT Friday morning.
Australia has made it to the semi-final of the T20 World Cup where they will meet unbeaten Group 2 winners, Pakistan.
Australia bucked expectations by finishing second in Group 1, recording four wins and just one defeat.
Pakistan have ridden a wave of euphoria all the way to the semis, remaining unbeaten in the tournament.
The toss is crucial in Dubai, with 10 out of 11 World Cup matches won by the team batting second.
Spinners are expected to play a significant role in the match, with Adam Zampa being a key player for Australia.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The average first innings score at Dubai in this tournament is 122, skewed by some low scores from West Indies, Bangladesh, and Scotland.
Australia has played three games in Dubai this World Cup, winning two and losing one.
Pakistan has won more T20 games in Dubai than any other team, with 16 wins from 27 games.
Australia and Pakistan have met seven times in Dubai, with Pakistan winning four times.
